Vice President Mike Pence spoke with Ecuadorian President Lenin Moreno to discuss the positive bilateral relationship between the United States and Ecuador. They acknowledged progress in areas such as security cooperation, counternarcotics efforts, and regional efforts to address the crisis in Venezuela. Pence commended Ecuador for steps taken to isolate the Maduro regime and support democracy and human rights in Venezuela. He also expressed support for Ecuador's economic reform agenda and encouraged continued efforts to cut spending and promote transparency.